Description: Mould-made pottery `Frog Type' lamp with two nozzles and a substantial rim around the filling-hole. At the rear are the head and forelegs of an animal, perhaps a frog. Each nozzle is defined by two grooves and is decorated with a branch pattern. Within the base-ring is a circular groove.
Bibliographic references: Lamp / Catalogue of the Lamps in the British Museum (Q2143)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Wellcome Institute for the History of Medicine (trustees)
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Sir Henry Solomon Wellcome
